Event description

Description

USE PROMO CODE "TRANCE" FOR
$5 OFF TICKETS TODAY ONLY

JOHN ASKEW (4 HOUR SET)

John Askew is a tech/trance producer/dj From The UK. After the huge success of his debut single "Vellum" in 2001, he has delivered release after release of consistently high quality club music - either through his own Discover label or via one of his many remixes for high profile labels such as Duty Free, Ministry of Sound, Euphonic and Paul van Dyk's legendary Vandit. Today, John has taken a step back from the running of Discover in order to concentrate on his new project - Kompressed Recordings. With Discover often being credited in the press as a trend setting label that separates itself from the 'run of the mill' commercial pop-trance that has flooded the UK market in the last 5 years, there are now a huge number of industry people and Discover fans keen to hear what the opening releases of Kompressed will deliver.

18+ Welcome | VIP 21+ ONLY

ALL TICKET SALES ARE FINAL. No refunds or exchanges.
**Prices do not reflect door pricing**
